editorialSummary.text: Wildlife sanctuary featuring over 100 tigers, plus safari tours & forest rest houses.

text.text: This is the other side of Corbett park which is also called Kalagarh. One of the most thrilling safari ride I ever took. I would rate it better than any other safari ride that I have taken on Ramnagar side of Corbett Tiger Reserve. The terrain goes up and down the mountain and many river crossing which made is much thrilling as compared to Ramnagar corbett drive which is usually plain. Animal sighting is hard I would say as compared to Ramnagar side as this side has much dense forest and rugged terrain. Please book through official website only and in advance as there is much less number of safari permits in a day if I compare with Ramnagar side. No food options available inside the park.

text.text: This was a wonderful safari! Our tour guide Anil was very educated and knew every bird in the park! We saw multiple different species of flora and fauna. The tours were conveniently set up and I would recommend to anyone looking to get out into Jim Corbette National Park!! If Anil is your guide, your in wonderful hands!!

text.text:
Supposedly, it's the 2nd largest church in Asia. Since we like to explore all kind of places of significance so we decided to visit it on our way from Landsdown to Haridwar. It's certainly a massive structure surrounding by a well maintained garden and lawn. However, church opens at 5pm and one of the staff was very rude to us when we entered in the wrong gate by mistake.

Overall, nothing great to visit.. you should rather visit St. Johans and St. Marrys church both built more than 100 years ago.

text.text:
It is the oldest temple present in Devi road, Kotdwara. The road also took its name from the temple itself. Inside the temple there is the Devi Mata statue and Shivling along with Radhe Krishna bhagwaan.
On the backside there is a banyan tree which is interconnected with a peepal tree also for Shani bhagwan Puja and Hanuman ji Murti also located in the front of The Tree.
This place is easy to commute and you can park your vehicles outside the temple on the other side of the road.
Jai Mata Di
